Police have swooped on one of their most wanted and a man linked to multiple murders, including two at the notorious Glebelands Hostel.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said a joint operation by various police units led to the man’s arrest on Christmas Eve.
“He was linked to two murder cases at Glebelands Hostel as well as other murders cases in the Bhekithemba area,” he said, “In one of the murder cases he was linked to, Tholakele Ngcangcatha was shot and killed at the hostel on August 3”.
READ: Glebelands report a 'cut and paste'
Zwane said when the man was arrested, he was found him in possession of an unlicensed pistol with 15 rounds of ammunition.
“He was charged for possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition and he is expected to appear in the Umlazi Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday,” he said.
KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner Major General Bheki Langa welcomed the man’s arrest.
“This is a  great effort by police in tracing all those who were allegedly involved in these killings at Glebelands Hostel, making the lives of the residents miserable,” he said, “Our police officers deployed in the hostel will continue with their operations in making sure that there is peace and stability at hostel”.
